==English==
===Phrasal verb===
'''to [[learn]] the [[ropes]]''' or '''[[know]] the [[ropes]]'''
#{{nautical}} to learn the [[basics]] or master [[introductory]] knowledge. Originally, the phrase "he knows the ropes" written on a seaman's discharge meant that he was only a novice, familiar with the principal ropes.
#:''Work slowly and cautiously until you have '''learned the ropes'''.''